<TITLE> Mohiuddin gets official AL nod </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 22 (bdnews24.com)  ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury has secured formal backing from ruling Awami League as Chittagong mayoral candidate. The decision came in a meeting of the ruling party's central working committee at the Ganabhaban, which began at 5pm on Saturday. AL general secretary Syed Ashraful Islam told bdnews24.com, "The decision was unanimous." Ashraf also urged all pro-liberation forces to come forward in Mohiuddin's support to ensure his win. Mohiuddin is contending the CCC polls under the banner of a pro-AL Nagorik Committee. Pro-BNP contender for the mayor's office M Manzur Alam, under the banner of Chittagong Unnayan Shangram Parishad, has been marked as Mohiuddin's main competition. Chittagong metropolitan BNP chief and the party's central advisory committee member Amir Khoshru Mahmud Chowdhury revealed his party's support for Manzur in a press conference in Chittagong on Friday. The Chittagong City Corporation elections are scheduled on June 17 when Mohiuddin will be seeking an unprecedented fourth term as the port city's mayor. b
